Upstream
--------

Wine is developed by the Wine project (https://www.winehq.org/). The
specific source tree calimocho builds from is the LGPL "FOSS code"
distribution published by CodeWeavers (https://www.codeweavers.com/),
who back the majority of upstream Wine development on macOS.

The exact upstream tarball used to produce this binary is pinned in
the calimocho repository at:

    versions.json -> cx_sources.url
    versions.json -> cx_sources.sha256

You can verify and re-download it with:

    jq -r '.cx_sources.url'    versions.json   # the URL
    jq -r '.cx_sources.sha256' versions.json   # the expected sha256

Modifications
-------------

calimocho does not modify Wine source files in-tree. All
modifications are kept as standalone unified-diff patches under:

    scripts/patches/

in the calimocho git repository, and are applied at build time by
`scripts/patch-sources.sh`. Each calimocho release tag (vX.Y.Z) in
git pins the exact patch set that produced that release's binary.

Corresponding source
--------------------

The complete corresponding source for the Wine portion of this
binary is, by construction:

    (1) the CodeWeavers tarball at versions.json -> cx_sources.url
        (verified against versions.json -> cx_sources.sha256), PLUS

    (2) the patches under scripts/patches/ at the calimocho git
        tag matching this binary release, available at
        https://github.com/dragoshont/calimocho

This satisfies the "corresponding source" requirement of LGPL §6.

Written offer (LGPL §6(b))
--------------------------

For any binary release of calimocho, for a period of at least three
(3) years from the date of that release, the calimocho maintainer
offers to provide the complete corresponding source code for the
Wine portion on a physical medium (USB stick, mailed at our cost) to
anyone who requests it. To request, open an issue at:

    https://github.com/dragoshont/calimocho/issues

with the title "LGPL source request: vX.Y.Z" and a postal address.
This offer is valid to any third party in possession of the binary.

